<item>
            <title>[METAMODEL-194] Max rows property of query cannot be 0</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/METAMODEL-194</link>
                <project id="12314523" key="METAMODEL">Apache MetaModel (Retired)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Query.setMaxRows(Integer) has a check to see that the value is correct. But for some reason it does not allow max rows = 0. In my opinion it should be possible to define and execute a query with max rows = 0. It would just always return an empty DataSet. But from our perspective we shouldn&apos;t prohibit it becuase the query may be created by some tool or dynamic code in which case allowing 0 may make sense.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
